<div class="content"><nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/foodtruck/">Food Trucks</a> › Food Truck Wraps Chicago</nav><h1>Food Truck Wraps in Chicago</h1><p class="lead speakable">Chicago Fleet Wraps creates stunning food truck wraps for restaurants, caterers, and mobile food vendors across Chicago. Your food truck is your storefront — make it impossible to ignore at festivals, street corners, and events. We use Avery Dennison MPI 1105 and 3M IJ180-CV3 cast vinyl with FDA-compliant, food-safe overlaminate and heat-resistant adhesive rated for kitchen-adjacent surfaces. 2-year workmanship warranty included.</p><div class="cta-bar"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/estimate/">Get a Food Truck Wrap Quote →</a><a class="btn" href="tel:+13125971286" style="border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--gold)">📞 Call Now</a></div><div class="trust"><span>📅 <strong>24+ Years</strong> Experience</span><span>🏆 <strong>9,400+</strong> Vehicles Wrapped</span><span>✅ <strong>Avery &amp; 3M</strong> Certified</span><span>🍽️ <strong>FDA-Compliant</strong> Materials</span><span>🚐 <strong>Free Pickup</strong></span></div><img alt="Blondies Beef food truck wrap by Chicago Fleet Wraps — custom food truck graphics Chicago" loading="lazy" src="/images/blondies_beef_truck.webp" style="width:100%;border-radius:8px;margin:0 0 24px"/><h2>Why Chicago Food Trucks Need Great Wraps</h2><p class="body-text">Chicago's food truck scene is one of the most competitive in the country. From Wacker Drive lunch spots to Navy Pier events and suburban festivals, your food truck competes against dozens of other vendors for attention. A professionally wrapped food truck with bold colors, appetizing photography, and clear branding draws customers from 50+ feet away — before they can even smell the food.</p><p class="body-text">Beyond events, your food truck is a moving billboard. Driving to and from events, parked in commissary lots, and posted on social media — your wrap generates tens of thousands of impressions daily. Many food truck operators report their wrap pays for itself within the first month of increased sales.</p><h2>Food Truck Wrap Services</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Full Food Truck Wraps</strong> — Every panel covered with vibrant, eye-catching graphics. $4,200–$8,000.</li><li><strong>Menu Board Graphics</strong> — Printed menu panels for serving windows. $400–$1,200.</li><li><strong>Serving Window Wraps</strong> — Counter and awning graphics that complete the look.</li><li><strong>Partial Wraps &amp; Accents</strong> — Cost-effective branding for tight budgets. $1,500–$3,000.</li><li><strong>Food Trailer Wraps</strong> — Enclosed trailers for catering and event operations.</li><li><strong>Catering Van Wraps</strong> — Cargo and sprinter van wraps for catering delivery fleets.</li></ul><h2>Food Truck Wrap Pricing</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Full Food Truck Wrap</strong> — $4,200–$8,000 depending on truck size and design complexity.</li><li><strong>Partial Wrap</strong> — $1,500–$3,000 for accent graphics and key panels.</li><li><strong>Menu Board Graphics</strong> — $400–$1,200 for printed serving window panels.</li><li><strong>Food Trailer Full Wrap</strong> — $2,500–$5,000 for enclosed trailers.</li><li><strong>Catering Van Wrap</strong> — $2,800–$4,500 for cargo and sprinter vans.</li></ul><p class="body-text">All food truck wraps are <strong>100% tax deductible</strong> under IRS Section 179 as a business advertising expense.</p>
