<h2>Food Truck Design Process</h2><p class="body-text">Our in-house design team specializes in food truck graphics that sell. We photograph your truck, create exact-scale templates, and produce full-color mockups showing how your wrap will look from every angle. We incorporate your logo, menu highlights, social media handles, and contact information into a cohesive design that works at speed and at rest. <a href="/fleet-wraps-chicago/" style="color:var(--gold)">Learn about our design process →</a></p><h2>Food Truck Types We Wrap</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Step Vans</strong> — Classic food truck chassis. Full coverage including serving side.</li><li><strong>Box Trucks</strong> — 14–22 ft converted food trucks with custom cutouts.</li><li><strong>Trailers</strong> — Enclosed food trailers for catering and festivals.</li><li><strong>Sprinter Vans</strong> — Coffee trucks, dessert trucks, and pop-up vendors.</li><li><strong>Cargo Vans</strong> — Catering delivery and mobile food prep.</li></ul><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="faq-item"><h3>How much does a food truck wrap cost in Chicago?</h3><p>Food truck full wraps range from $4,200–$8,000 depending on truck size, design complexity, and number of serving windows. Partial wraps start at $1,500. Menu board graphics start at $400.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Are food truck wraps food-safe?</h3><p>Yes. All food truck wraps use FDA-compliant, food-safe overlaminate. We use heat-resistant adhesive for surfaces near grills, fryers, and steam — ensuring the wrap stays in place and doesn't contaminate food contact areas.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does a food truck wrap last?</h3><p>Our food truck wraps use premium cast vinyl rated for 5–7 years of outdoor durability. The overlaminate protects against grease splatter, steam, and UV exposure. Regular cleaning extends wrap life significantly.</p></div><div class="faq-item"><h3>Can you wrap around serving windows and equipment?</h3><p>Yes. We template every food truck individually to account for serving windows, exhaust vents, generators, and equipment. The wrap is precision-cut to fit around every component for a seamless, professional finish.</p></div><div class="cta-bar"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/estimate/">Get Your Food Truck Wrap Quote →</a><a class="btn" href="tel:+13125971286" style="border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--gold)">📞 (312) 597-1286</a></div></div>